people in uniform who are in the
distinct minority.

246
00:12:36,381 --> 00:12:38,800
Oh my gosh! What if Mio is the
only one!?

247
00:12:38,842 --> 00:12:44,347
"Oh, see that girl there, she's
the only one here who's wearing
a uniform!"

248
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:47,058
Quit it!

249
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:49,769
It said we can wear whatever
we want, so it's really
no big deal!

250
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:51,813
[Tsumugi] Good morning!

251
00:12:54,065 --> 00:12:56,484
It took ages to get changed this
morning.

252
00:12:56,526 --> 00:12:58,069
[All three] G-Good morning...

253
00:12:58,111 --> 00:13:01,031
Wow, Mugi-chan looks like
she's going to the beach!

254
00:13:01,072 --> 00:13:04,451
Wait, is everyone going
to the beach after class?!

255
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:05,994
That isn't on the schedule.

256
00:13:06,036 --> 00:13:07,787
Let's hurry in, shall we?

257
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:12,625
Hey Mugi!

258
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:14,586
Yes?

259
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,546
You left the tag on your dress.

260
00:13:16,588 --> 00:13:18,214
And with this outfit,

261
00:13:18,256 --> 00:13:20,925
wouldn't going without socks
look a whole lot better than
this?

262
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:23,511
(huffing)

263
00:13:24,721 --> 00:13:27,557
(gasps) <i>Wait, don't tell me she-</i>

264
00:13:27,599 --> 00:13:30,560
I'd like you to whack me on the
head!

265
00:13:30,602 --> 00:13:32,437
Um, you know, it really hurts.

266
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:34,981
I want you to do it to me
anyway!

267
00:13:35,023 --> 00:13:38,234
If you're that dead set on it,
I guess I can do it.

268
00:13:38,276 --> 00:13:39,444
You can?

269
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:41,071
Just a little tap, right?

270
00:13:41,112 --> 00:13:44,282
Whenever you're ready!

271
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:47,327
[Ritsu] You're not being watched
by a security detail, are you?

272
00:13:47,369 --> 00:13:49,788
[Tsumugi] There aren't any!
Don't worry!

273
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,247
[Ritsu] Then here goes!

274
00:13:51,289 --> 00:13:52,457
[Tsumugi] Ready!

275
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:55,543
[Ritsu] Um...

276
00:13:55,585 --> 00:13:57,671
Maybe I'll go with a chop?

277
00:13:57,712 --> 00:14:00,131
[Tsumugi] Do it as hard as you
like!

278
00:14:05,637 --> 00:14:07,514
[Ritsu] Whack?

279
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:09,349
I can't do it! Forget it!

280
00:14:09,391 --> 00:14:11,351
Huh?

281
00:14:11,393 --> 00:14:14,020
[Ritsu] It doesn't work if
someone ASKS you to. It has to
be spontaneous, okay?

282
00:14:14,062 --> 00:14:15,855
[Tsumugi] Spontaneous?

283
00:14:15,897 --> 00:14:18,942
Yeah! I can't whack you in the
head if you haven't done
anything wrong.

284
00:14:18,983 --> 00:14:21,403
But if you were to do
something incredibly ditzy,

285
00:14:21,444 --> 00:14:23,780
I'd straighten you out
right then and there!

286
00:14:23,822 --> 00:14:25,198
Ditzy huh?

287
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,534
[Yui] Right? Nodoka-chan was
crazy to do that, right?

288
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:30,161
When you offer somebody
a bite of your cake, they
don't...

289
00:14:30,203 --> 00:14:32,872
<i>[Ritsu] Mugi couldn't</i>
<i>possibly be trying-</i>
[Yui] ...eat the strawberry
on top!

290
00:14:32,914 --> 00:14:34,457
[Mio] Sure she's not
just messing with you?

291
00:14:34,499 --> 00:14:37,293
I remember one time when Ritsu
ate the strawberry on my cake,

292
00:14:37,335 --> 00:14:41,297
and I whacked her so I can
understand how you feel, but
still...

293
00:14:41,339 --> 00:14:43,591
[Yui] Nodoka-chan ate it,
just as casual as can be!

294
00:14:43,633 --> 00:14:45,010
<i>[Ritsu] No doubt about it.</i>

295
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:50,306
I guess we should look through
their study guides first.

296
00:14:50,348 --> 00:14:52,642
[Yui] I wonder if there are any
books that say that eating makes
you smarter?

297
00:14:52,684 --> 00:14:53,685
[Ritsu] Mugi, over here.

298
00:14:53,727 --> 00:14:54,978
[Mio] Yeah, as if.

299
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:58,023
I knew it, you're trying
to be a class clown.

300
00:14:58,064 --> 00:14:59,524
Did I do it wrong?

301
00:14:59,566 --> 00:15:01,943
I thought that this would be
the least appropriate outfit

302
00:15:01,985 --> 00:15:04,362
to wear for our summer classes.

303
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:07,824
I'm afraid it's just too vague
and uncommitted to really work.

304
00:15:07,866 --> 00:15:13,371
For a gag like that to work,
it has to be totally in your
face.

305
00:15:13,413 --> 00:15:15,040
[Tsumugi] Sure is hot today,
Mio-chan.

306
00:15:15,081 --> 00:15:16,416
Of course it is!

307
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:18,251
[Tsumugi] Ah, I see!
[Ritsu] Hey, don't take notes!

308
00:15:18,293 --> 00:15:22,339
Are you really that eager to get
whacked upside the head, Mugi?

309
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:24,674
[Tsumugi] You and Mio-chan are
always express your affection

310
00:15:24,716 --> 00:15:26,343
in intimate, physical ways.

311
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:28,762
So do Yui-chan and Azusa-chan.

312
00:15:28,803 --> 00:15:32,057
I'm the only one who doesn't
have that kind of intimate bond!

313
00:15:32,098 --> 00:15:34,142
Though I love being physically
intimate!

314
00:15:34,184 --> 00:15:37,896
Don't you think you're
obsessing a little here?

315
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:41,483
All right, Mugi. If you're
really that determined, I'll
help you out.

316
00:15:41,524 --> 00:15:42,567
You mean it?!

317
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:44,444
Now the key is a total lack of
shame!

318
00:15:44,486 --> 00:15:47,572
Once you start a gag, you commit
and see it through to the bitter
end!

319
00:15:47,614 --> 00:15:49,074
[Ritsu] Understood?!
[Tsumugi] Yes, ma' am!

320
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:51,409
I have to say, I'm kind of
surprised that,

321
00:15:51,451 --> 00:15:53,703
you and Ritsu decided to go to
college.

322
00:15:53,745 --> 00:15:57,540
Well, Sawa-chan told us that it
was way too late to start job
hunting.

323
00:15:57,582 --> 00:15:59,250
So we might as well try.

324
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:02,712
It's also a little late to begin
studying for college entrance
exams.

325
00:16:02,754 --> 00:16:04,714
Oo, headbands!

326
00:16:04,756 --> 00:16:06,508
Ready?

327
00:16:06,549 --> 00:16:07,967
[Tsumugi] Mio!

328
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:11,763
I will pass my exams for sure!

329
00:16:11,805 --> 00:16:12,889
Quit goofing around!

330
00:16:12,931 --> 00:16:15,058
Yes! So will I, Mio-chan!

331
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,059
[Mio] Mugi?

332
00:16:16,101 --> 00:16:17,769
Those look great on you.

333
00:16:17,811 --> 00:16:20,647
Why in the world would you
put on normal glasses?!

334
00:16:20,689 --> 00:16:24,734
It's so blazingly bright in here
that I can't read anything!

335
00:16:24,776 --> 00:16:28,071
Yui, look really close.
If you squint real hard at it,

336
00:16:28,113 --> 00:16:31,574
the words will suddenly pop out
of this long passage and you'll
see it.

337
00:16:31,616 --> 00:16:34,577
I saw it! I saw it and
it was the letter "a"!

338
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:36,037
You did not!

339
00:16:36,079 --> 00:16:37,831
I can see it, too.

340
00:16:37,872 --> 00:16:41,001
Judging from the context
surrounding this passage, the
answer is "a".

341
00:16:41,042 --> 00:16:43,086
Nicely done!

342
00:16:43,128 --> 00:16:45,088
Why did you say it so properly?

343
00:16:45,130 --> 00:16:47,841
Sorry, I couldn't help myself.

344
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:49,759
Your ID card is ready, Miss.

345
00:16:49,801 --> 00:16:54,347
I wish I'd brought a more
flattering picture with me this
one looks terrible.

346
00:16:54,389 --> 00:16:55,724
Well mine turned out pretty
good!

347
00:16:55,765 --> 00:16:58,393
[Ritsu] I'm rather shy
and reserved, you see.

348
00:16:58,435 --> 00:17:00,812
This is not a place for goofing
off!

349
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:02,397
<i>You're on!</i>

350
00:17:02,897 --> 00:17:04,357
Here is mine!

351
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:07,152
<i>Yes! That should work!</i>

352
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:11,281
[Mio] Oh, I get it. You two just
put stickers over the picture.

353
00:17:11,322 --> 00:17:12,949
Your eyes are half-closed.

354
00:17:12,991 --> 00:17:14,325
What the heck were you
thinking?!

355
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:15,952
[Ritsu] The normal one
was funnier!
[Tsumugi] It was?

356
00:17:15,994 --> 00:17:18,038
[Yui] Look! Look!
[Mio] Your sister?!

357
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:21,291
Heh. I kind of submitted
her picture by mistake.

358
00:17:21,332 --> 00:17:25,587
Wow, you know,
you just can't beat fresh ditz.

359
00:17:25,628 --> 00:17:28,298
I tried! I tried so hard! I
don't get it!

360
00:17:28,340 --> 00:17:29,841
I know that you're trying your
hardest,

361
00:17:29,883 --> 00:17:32,469
but it's gonna be a lot harder
than I thought it would be,

362
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:33,970
to get you whacked in the head.

363
00:17:34,012 --> 00:17:37,307
And it'll take a lot to get Mio
to whack YOU, of all people.

364
00:17:37,349 --> 00:17:39,267
May even be impossible...

365
00:17:39,309 --> 00:17:40,852
Oh look, there they are!

366
00:17:40,894 --> 00:17:42,687
You're right!
Thanks for waiting for me!

367
00:17:42,729 --> 00:17:43,646
Sure.

368
00:17:43,688 --> 00:17:45,106
Come on, Let's go home!

369
00:17:46,566 --> 00:17:48,818
[Mio] You do remember that
tomorrow is a school day, right?

370
00:17:48,860 --> 00:17:53,323
[Yui] Of course I remember!
It'll be so great to see
everybody in class again!

371
00:17:53,365 --> 00:17:55,283
[Mio] It sure will.

372
00:18:01,456 --> 00:18:03,667
Looks like there's
an extra piece of cake...

373
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:06,795
It'll be kinda hard to
divide this into fifths.

374
00:18:06,836 --> 00:18:08,296
[Mio] Rock-paper-scissors?

375
00:18:08,338 --> 00:18:11,341
Come on, no way, I'm terrible
at that stupid game.

376
00:18:11,383 --> 00:18:15,679
[Yui] Alright! Then let's settle
it the old fashioned way!

377
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:18,098
Very well, I'll take you on.

378
00:18:18,139 --> 00:18:20,809
Oh, Okay! The winner
gets the cake!

379
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:24,062
And the loser gets a forehead
flick from everyone here
in the room!

380
00:18:24,104 --> 00:18:25,313
A forehead flick?!

381
00:18:25,355 --> 00:18:26,815
Oo, yeah let's do it!

382
00:18:26,856 --> 00:18:29,859
Throw the game! If you lose,
you'll get smacked for sure!

383
00:18:29,901 --> 00:18:31,027
I got it!

384
00:18:31,069 --> 00:18:32,821
[Ritsu] Okay, let's start!

385
00:18:32,862 --> 00:18:35,573
I'll get it going! Ready, five!

386
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:37,951
Ready, set, uh three!

387
00:18:37,992 --> 00:18:39,327
Ready, seven!

388
00:18:39,369 --> 00:18:40,995
[Mio] Ready, one!

389
00:18:41,037 --> 00:18:42,539
[Tsumugi] Ready, two!

390
00:18:49,713 --> 00:18:52,257
Who loses at a game
they suggested?

391
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:55,844
I'm so jealous, Mugi-chan...

392
00:18:55,885 --> 00:18:58,471
Well, let's eat quickly
and get on to practicing.

393
00:18:58,513 --> 00:19:01,307
Yeah, I finally get to
have my strawberry today,

394
00:19:01,349 --> 00:19:03,393
so I won't even put up
a fight this time.

395
00:19:03,435 --> 00:19:07,480
I remember when Ritsu ate
the strawberry on my cake,
and I whacked her.

396
00:19:07,522 --> 00:19:09,566
So I understand how you feel.

397
00:19:27,959 --> 00:19:29,502
Nodoka-chan!

398
00:19:29,544 --> 00:19:31,254
[Nodoka] What on earth
is the matter?

399
00:19:31,296 --> 00:19:33,048
Just look at her!

400
00:19:33,089 --> 00:19:36,051
She had her strawberry stolen,
and she's heartbroken!
She's in tears!

401
00:19:36,092 --> 00:19:39,387
You see, that's how important
the strawberry is, Nodoka-chan!

402
00:19:39,429 --> 00:19:42,557
[Nodoka] I apologize for
hurting your feelings, then.

403
00:19:42,599 --> 00:19:45,226
[Yui] You finally understand,
Nodoka-chan!

404
00:19:45,268 --> 00:19:48,021
Mio-chan, I'm so sorry.

405
00:19:48,063 --> 00:19:49,314
[Mio] You want to be hit?

406
00:19:49,356 --> 00:19:51,983
[Tsumugi] I'm sorry,
I know how silly it sounds.

407
00:19:52,025 --> 00:19:56,029
No way, this is all Mio's fault
for not reacting to any of your
gags.

408
00:19:56,071 --> 00:19:57,947
What!? It is not!

409
00:19:57,989 --> 00:20:01,785
You really should have just said
something to me about this in
the first place!

410
00:20:01,826 --> 00:20:03,745
You just want a love tap, right?

411
00:20:03,787 --> 00:20:05,080
Y-You'll do it?

412
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:07,290
Sure, I guess it's not that big
a deal.

413
00:20:07,332 --> 00:20:09,376
Gie tos, Mio-chan!

414
00:20:09,417 --> 00:20:11,378
Seriously, where are you from?

415
00:20:12,170 --> 00:20:13,463
Okay! Whenever you are ready!

416
00:20:13,505 --> 00:20:16,716
You are one strange girl...

417
00:20:16,758 --> 00:20:18,134
Uh...

418
00:20:20,303 --> 00:20:25,558
(heart beating)

419
00:20:26,518 --> 00:20:29,145
Wow, she's really tense,
isn't she?

420
00:20:32,023 --> 00:20:34,442
Why'd you hit me?!

421
00:20:34,484 --> 00:20:37,821
[Ritsu] I guess nothing
worked... I'm really sorry.

422
00:20:37,862 --> 00:20:39,948
No, I should be the
one apologizing to you.

423
00:20:39,989 --> 00:20:42,867
I mean, it was a very odd
request I made.

424
00:20:42,909 --> 00:20:47,247
If you just want to be bonked on
the head, there ought to be a
way to get it done...

425
00:20:47,288 --> 00:20:48,456
For instance...

426
00:20:48,498 --> 00:20:51,668
Thanks, Ri-chan,
but I'm giving up on that.

427
00:20:51,710 --> 00:20:53,336
Really?

428
00:20:53,378 --> 00:20:56,506
[Tsumugi] Oh, dear. You have
a welt on your forehead.

429
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:03,221
You know, you really make
an excellent escort, Ri-chan.

430
00:21:03,263 --> 00:21:07,100
You're so sweet, and I know that
you would do just about anything
to help a friend.

431
00:21:07,142 --> 00:21:10,729
If you were a boy,
the girls would all be lining up
for you.

432
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:12,439
(gasps)

433
00:21:13,189 --> 00:21:15,692
(embarassed)

434
00:21:15,734 --> 00:21:17,652
[Ritsu] How am I supposed
to respond to that?!

435
00:21:17,694 --> 00:21:19,654
(whacks Tsumugi)
[Tsumugi] Ouch!

436
00:21:24,325 --> 00:21:26,494
[Ritsu] Yeah. Sorry about that.

437
00:21:26,536 --> 00:21:28,371
Well, you remember when I called
you

438
00:21:28,413 --> 00:21:30,832
and asked if you wanted
to go hang out that day?

439
00:21:30,874 --> 00:21:33,084
I ran into Mugi right after
that, and-

440
00:21:33,126 --> 00:21:38,882
Huh? Where did we go? Candy
store, a game center, that kind
of thing.

441
00:21:38,923 --> 00:21:42,844
Mugi was funny, she was totally
into everything like a little
kid.

442
00:21:42,886 --> 00:21:43,803
(chuckles)

443
00:21:43,845 --> 00:21:45,764
Admittedly, she's always
like that.

444
00:21:45,805 --> 00:21:49,893
And then she was like, "I want
to be whacked on the head!"
Can you believe it?

445
00:21:49,934 --> 00:21:53,772
That kind of thing has to be
spontaneous, you know? So I-

446
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:55,940
Oops. Mio are you there?

447
00:21:55,982 --> 00:21:59,319
Um, why aren't you talking?
Are you mad at me?

448
00:21:59,361 --> 00:22:01,112
[Mio] Why?

449
00:22:01,154 --> 00:22:03,990
[Mio] Why didn't you invite me
to come along with you two
that day?!

450
00:22:04,032 --> 00:22:07,410
[Mio] I wanted to hang out
with Mugi, too!

451
00:22:08,536 --> 00:22:10,538
I DID invite you.

452
00:22:15,085 --> 00:22:16,878
(giggles)

453
00:22:20,256 --> 00:22:25,887
(closing song, "NO, Thank You!")

454
00:23:50,555 --> 00:23:52,766
[Principal] The long summer
vacation is now over

455
00:23:52,807 --> 00:23:55,643
and new school term is
once again upon us.

456
00:23:55,685 --> 00:23:57,562
It gives me no end of joy to see

457
00:23:57,604 --> 00:24:01,524
all your tanned, healthy faces
here once again after such a
long time away.

458
00:24:01,566 --> 00:24:04,069
I trust you all feel the same
joy in being back here.

459
00:24:04,110 --> 00:24:07,072
The experiences you gain
during high school are...

460
00:24:07,113 --> 00:24:12,869
[Yui] I don't understand, why do
we have to run a whole 42.195
kilometers?

461
00:24:12,911 --> 00:24:14,162
Unique flavor...

462
00:24:14,204 --> 00:24:16,164
That's it! That's what we'll do!

463
00:24:16,206 --> 00:24:20,460
The marathon will be cancelled,
and we'll have a red bean soup
contest instead!

